1072	    /// If an operation becomes ready, its index is returned. If multiple operations are ready at
1073	    /// the same time, a random one among them is chosen. If none of the operations become ready
1074	    /// for the specified duration, an error is returned.
1075	    ///
1076	    /// An operation is considered to be ready if it doesn't have to block. Note that it is ready
1077	    /// even when it will simply return an error because the channel is disconnected.
1078	    ///
1079	    /// Note that this method might return with success spuriously, so it's a good idea to double
1080	    /// check if the operation is really ready.
1081	    ///
